description: Web component architecture standards
globs:
  - "ui/src/components/**"
---

- Read `docs/standards/design/design-system.md` and `docs/standards/design/ux-patterns.md` for component architecture.
- Component tag: `hu-<name>` prefix, registered with `@customElement("hu-<name>")`
- Base class: LitElement with `static styles = css\`...\``
- All styles must use `--hu-*` tokens — no raw hex, px spacing, or font-family
- ARIA: every interactive component needs `role`, `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby`
- Focus: visible focus ring using `outline: 2px solid var(--hu-accent)` on `:focus-visible`
- Keyboard: support Tab, Escape (for overlays), Enter/Space (for buttons), Arrow keys (for lists/tabs)
- Every new component MUST have: (1) test in `components.test.ts`, (2) entry in `catalog.html`, (3) TypeScript types in `HTMLElementTagNameMap`
- Events fire upward via `CustomEvent`; data flows down via `@property`
- Use slots for composition, not string props for content

## Error & State Handling

- Every view/component that fetches data must handle 3 states: **loading** (skeleton), **populated**, **error**
- Use `<hu-toast>` for transient notifications (success, info); inline error banners for persistent failures
- Gateway errors: catch in the controller, surface to the view via a reactive `@state()` property
- Never show raw error messages to users — map to human-friendly text
- Never render a blank screen — always show at least a skeleton or error state
